OL,6,FThe melting of snow and glaciers also
OL,7,Fhas direct consequences on the
OL,8,Fstability of infrastructures built on
OL,9,Fit and contributes to an increasing
OL,10,Famount of carbon in the atmosphere,
OL,11,Faccording to the WMO.
OL,13,F"Ruined winter vacations and cancelled
OL,14,Fsports fixtures are ` literally ` the
OL,15,Ftip of the iceberg of climate change,"
OL,16,FWMO Secretary-General Celeste Saulo
OL,17,Fsaid.
